[{"_id":"676e382d-0eda-3f8c-99be-7fce7f855447","authorName":"Sam","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"","authorUri":"http://www.blogger.com/profile/11457234052102618582","authorUserId":"","authorFallbackAvatar":"","message":"Hello,  \r\nCan you give me sample example for 'how to close client socket properly?  \r\nIn my application when client exit(here I closed reader,writer and close socket) and when client start again client able to connect (BeginConnect() succeeds) but unable to send data to server(In such case I have to restart my server application to make it running).I guess client socket not closing properly.Please provide me solution.","postId":"2009_05_socket-operations-c853ed9d-6443-31ab-9258-c500d1643b90","replyTo":"","date":"2012-04-25T16:03:31Z","timestamp":1335369811},{"_id":"fc917233-5a5b-3b89-839d-7e66788f935a","authorName":"Stephen Cleary","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"3db7b6e14d9da42751e4bab03bc4d034","authorUri":"https://stephencleary.com/","authorUserId":"","authorFallbackAvatar":"","message":"The problem is with your server. If you close the client socket, then that's all you have to do.","postId":"2009_05_socket-operations-c853ed9d-6443-31ab-9258-c500d1643b90","replyTo":"","date":"2012-04-25T16:45:45Z","timestamp":1335372345},{"_id":"91944bb6-edd1-36f2-80fd-eee582197be9","authorName":"Sam","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"","authorUri":"http://www.blogger.com/profile/11457234052102618582","authorUserId":"","authorFallbackAvatar":"","message":"Thanks for the reply.  \r\nBut how to handle such scenario, so that client will connect properly and data will transfer properly.  \r\nI have implemented Keep alive.  \r\nPlease provide some basic steps to achieve this.","postId":"2009_05_socket-operations-c853ed9d-6443-31ab-9258-c500d1643b90","replyTo":"","date":"2012-04-26T09:51:20Z","timestamp":1335433880},{"_id":"2934018b-76d2-314b-a7a0-cff4b0464587","authorName":"Stephen Cleary","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"3db7b6e14d9da42751e4bab03bc4d034","authorUri":"https://stephencleary.com/","authorUserId":"","authorFallbackAvatar":"","message":"I'm sorry, Sam, but there are no basic steps.  \r\n\r\nI recommend reading my TCP/IP blog posts, and then reading the items listed in the Resources blog post: [http://nitoprograms.blogspot.com/2009/05/tcpip-resources.html](http://nitoprograms.blogspot.com/2009/05/tcpip-resources.html)  \r\n\r\nThen you'll have enough information to design a custom TCP/IP protocol.  \r\n\r\nIf you want a simpler solution, you could use Web API, WCF, or .NET remoting.","postId":"2009_05_socket-operations-c853ed9d-6443-31ab-9258-c500d1643b90","replyTo":"","date":"2012-04-27T02:23:15Z","timestamp":1335493395},{"_id":"a72c6cbc-737d-35c3-be3f-2935577ee2c9","authorName":"Sam","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"","authorUri":"http://www.blogger.com/profile/11457234052102618582","authorUserId":"","authorFallbackAvatar":"","message":"Thanks Stephen. I will read your TCP/IP blog posts.  \r\nAnd thanks for your suggestions I will also think on that.","postId":"2009_05_socket-operations-c853ed9d-6443-31ab-9258-c500d1643b90","replyTo":"","date":"2012-04-27T09:41:14Z","timestamp":1335519674},{"_id":"026dd671-aeca-3415-bfde-61422d0e1590","authorName":"ankita","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"92dc761b230b829ab2e4041806988bc9","authorUri":"","authorUserId":"disqus:disqus_ch5Oc6nGJ7","authorFallbackAvatar":"","message":"Hey Stephen.  \r\n I have one question. Where bind() comes in TCP/IP layer if we want to relate it. Because as per my knowledge about transport layer deal with port address thing and IP layer deal with IP address. And bind() works on both. I have really hard to get this things. But no luck... please help me with this.","postId":"2009_05_socket-operations-c853ed9d-6443-31ab-9258-c500d1643b90","replyTo":"","date":"2017-05-02T09:41:39Z","timestamp":1493718099},{"_id":"16c78805-e8b0-3b27-b188-da221240ccdc","authorName":"Stephen Cleary","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"3db7b6e14d9da42751e4bab03bc4d034","authorUri":"https://stephencleary.com/","authorUserId":"","authorFallbackAvatar":"","message":"If you're talking about the OSI model, then you can (mostly) consider both TCP and IP as part of the transport layer. The OSI model isn't strictly followed, though; it's a nice abstraction but not performant enough to implement exactly.","postId":"2009_05_socket-operations-c853ed9d-6443-31ab-9258-c500d1643b90","replyTo":"026dd671-aeca-3415-bfde-61422d0e1590","date":"2017-05-02T12:20:39Z","timestamp":1493727639},{"_id":"5b85965e-cbdb-361f-9114-bac32be28ca9","authorName":"Stephen Cleary","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"3db7b6e14d9da42751e4bab03bc4d034","authorUri":"https://stephencleary.com/","authorUserId":"","authorFallbackAvatar":"","message":"I have no idea, sorry.","postId":"2009_05_socket-operations-c853ed9d-6443-31ab-9258-c500d1643b90","replyTo":"7c246643-e91f-39a7-9ca7-60521109efe6","date":"2017-05-25T11:07:25Z","timestamp":1495710445},{"_id":"7c246643-e91f-39a7-9ca7-60521109efe6","authorName":"ankita","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"4535d620675491aa061ce60d2b94981a","authorUri":"","authorUserId":"disqus:disqus_5R54HBx5me","authorFallbackAvatar":"","message":"One more question.I was working with unix domain socket which is one type of IPC. So, I want to know some real time application which are using UNIX Domain socket for same host communication. If you have any idea about this.","postId":"2009_05_socket-operations-c853ed9d-6443-31ab-9258-c500d1643b90","replyTo":"","date":"2017-05-25T08:19:35Z","timestamp":1495700375}]